(After long, hard thought, he decided to save himself.)

1529
00:54:20,149 --> 00:54:21,218
"Se."

1530
00:54:21,219 --> 00:54:24,319
(He decided to betray Se Yoon in the end!)

1531
00:54:24,449 --> 00:54:25,518
- Joon!
- Se Yoon is...

1532
00:54:25,519 --> 00:54:27,789
(The rat-hunting alliance was doomed in the end.)

1533
00:54:27,889 --> 00:54:29,288
How did this happen?

1534
00:54:29,289 --> 00:54:32,758
(Joon chose to sleep indoors instead of making DinDin sleep outdoors.)

1535
00:54:32,759 --> 00:54:35,529
We let DinDin outsmart us again!

1536
00:54:36,199 --> 00:54:37,569
How did this happen?

1537
00:54:37,699 --> 00:54:40,139
(Se Yoon will sleep outdoors.)

1538
00:54:40,339 --> 00:54:41,969
As a result of the game...

1539
00:54:43,069 --> 00:54:44,239
We missed him again.

1540
00:54:44,539 --> 00:54:45,978
(They failed to catch the rat.)

1541
00:54:45,979 --> 00:54:47,938
DinDin, how many bottles did you find?

1542
00:54:47,939 --> 00:54:49,809
- I eliminated Seon Ho.
- Yes.

1543
00:54:51,109 --> 00:54:53,018
And I eliminated Se Yoon...

1544
00:54:53,019 --> 00:54:55,019
by submitting "Yoon."

1545
00:54:56,189 --> 00:54:57,289
Who found "Se?"

1546
00:54:57,589 --> 00:54:58,719
I did.

1547
00:54:59,359 --> 00:55:01,489
(He finally found out about the traitor.)

1548
00:55:01,689 --> 00:55:03,689
- I found "Min."
- I found "Jong."

1549
00:55:04,389 --> 00:55:06,199
- That's all.
- You agreed to catch the rat.

1550
00:55:07,159 --> 00:55:08,928
- So we had another rat here.
- How could you do that?

1551
00:55:08,929 --> 00:55:10,168
These four and...

1552
00:55:10,169 --> 00:55:12,569
If you had waited until we found DinDin's Yakult...

1553
00:55:13,339 --> 00:55:16,339
I waited until the last minute before submitting it.

1554
00:55:16,769 --> 00:55:19,108
- Oh, I see.
- So, Jong Min didn't submit it...

1555
00:55:19,109 --> 00:55:21,379
right away so that he could eliminate me first.

1556
00:55:22,749 --> 00:55:24,178
(Whose is that?)

1557
00:55:24,179 --> 00:55:25,218
(It's a secret!)

1558
00:55:25,219 --> 00:55:27,395
(All the pieces of a puzzle are finally falling into place.)

1559
00:55:27,419 --> 00:55:29,619
- I'd like to say something.
- Go ahead.

1560
00:55:29,889 --> 00:55:32,558
No matter how hard the four of you tried to eliminate me...

1561
00:55:32,559 --> 00:55:34,718
- Just look at the result.
- Gosh. I'm so upset.

1562
00:55:34,719 --> 00:55:36,229
You must know if you see the result.

1563
00:55:37,629 --> 00:55:39,029
Let's have a 4-on-1 match sometime.

1564
00:55:39,399 --> 00:55:41,729
But exactly what did you guys do to eliminate me?

1565
00:55:42,769 --> 00:55:44,628
The four of us planned a strategy and everything.

1566
00:55:44,629 --> 00:55:46,499
Really? What did you do?

1567
00:55:46,969 --> 00:55:49,068
- All right.
- What a shame.

1568
00:55:49,069 --> 00:55:51,039
As a result of Track Yakult,

1569
00:55:53,009 --> 00:55:55,679
Jong Min, Se Yoon, and Seon Ho will...

1570
00:55:56,079 --> 00:55:57,209
sleep outdoors.

1571
00:55:58,619 --> 00:56:00,319
Gosh. We let the rat outsmart us again.

1572
00:56:00,979 --> 00:56:04,519
We've completed all of today's schedule, but...

1573
00:56:04,749 --> 00:56:06,588
"But?" Is there something left?

1574
00:56:06,589 --> 00:56:09,459
Before you go to sleep,

1575
00:56:11,389 --> 00:56:12,559
you will...

1576
00:56:12,899 --> 00:56:16,569
turn in your phones and watches.

1577
00:56:16,729 --> 00:56:18,128
- Why?
- I guess...

1578
00:56:18,129 --> 00:56:19,539
we'll do a time-based mission.

1579
00:56:20,199 --> 00:56:22,385
Maybe we'll have to wake up in two hours or something like that.

1580
00:56:22,409 --> 00:56:23,669
- So...
- Maybe.

1581
00:56:25,039 --> 00:56:27,138
All right. Everyone...

1582
00:56:27,139 --> 00:56:28,178
(I wonder what kind of mission it is.)

1583
00:56:28,179 --> 00:56:30,679
Tomorrow morning, the wake-up song...

1584
00:56:31,279 --> 00:56:34,379
- will start playing at 8:12am.
- What?

1585
00:56:34,449 --> 00:56:35,588
- What?
- What?

1586
00:56:35,589 --> 00:56:36,589
What?

1587
00:56:37,249 --> 00:56:39,189
(At 8:12am, not at 8am?)

1588
00:56:39,359 --> 00:56:41,719
When the wake-up song plays, you have to wake up...

1589
00:56:41,989 --> 00:56:43,389
and gather together outside.

1590
00:56:43,559 --> 00:56:46,558
Get ready for bed. You did a great job today.

1591
00:56:46,559 --> 00:56:48,259
- Thank you.
- Good job, everyone.

1592
00:56:48,329 --> 00:56:49,499
Thank you!

1593
00:56:49,599 --> 00:56:52,368
But it's... Really? I wonder what we'll be doing.

1594
00:56:52,369 --> 00:56:54,049
- Something doesn't feel right.
- Exactly.

1595
00:56:54,939 --> 00:56:56,638
Joon might stay up until 4am.

1596
00:56:56,639 --> 00:56:58,359
(What will they be doing the next morning?)

1597
00:56:58,439 --> 00:57:00,759
(After getting ready for bed, the members gathered again.)

1598
00:57:00,909 --> 00:57:02,449
Please turn in your phones.

1599
00:57:02,609 --> 00:57:05,348
- Let's go.
- This is my phone.

1600
00:57:05,349 --> 00:57:08,378
(The members turn in their phones in turns.)

1601
00:57:08,379 --> 00:57:09,649
Show me your arms.

1602
00:57:09,989 --> 00:57:12,358
- We're not hiding anything.
- Are you wearing a watch?

1603
00:57:12,359 --> 00:57:13,559
Please turn in your watch.

1604
00:57:14,159 --> 00:57:15,839
But I have my stomach to tell me the time.

1605
00:57:16,559 --> 00:57:18,129
- It's accurate.
- Of course.

1606
00:57:18,859 --> 00:57:20,098
Let me check for the last time.

1607
00:57:20,099 --> 00:57:21,258
- Come on.
- What?

1608
00:57:21,259 --> 00:57:23,268
- Must you really do this?
- That hurts my feelings.

1609
00:57:23,269 --> 00:57:24,269
Are we at an airport?

1610
00:57:24,270 --> 00:57:25,568
(The airport-level security check continues.)

1611
00:57:25,569 --> 00:57:27,539
There's no way I hid my phone here.

1612
00:57:28,339 --> 00:57:29,709
- Can we go to bed now?
- Yes.

1613
00:57:30,269 --> 00:57:31,269
Let's go to sleep now.

1614
00:57:31,270 --> 00:57:32,778
- Good night.
- Good night.

1615
00:57:32,779 --> 00:57:35,139
- Good night.
- Sweet dreams.

1616
00:57:35,309 --> 00:57:36,578
Bye.

1617
00:57:36,579 --> 00:57:39,259
(Exchanging their last goodbyes, drifting off into their own night)

1618
00:57:39,649 --> 00:57:40,649
Gosh, this is nice.

1619
00:57:40,849 --> 00:57:43,189
What was the strategy?

1620
00:57:43,289 --> 00:57:45,859
The four of them wanted to team up.

1621
00:57:46,859 --> 00:57:48,559
Then they wanted to look for yours.

1622
00:57:49,059 --> 00:57:51,228
They can't gang up on me like that.

1623
00:57:51,229 --> 00:57:52,729
They didn't have to go that far.

1624
00:57:53,299 --> 00:57:55,029
You can just team up with me.

1625
00:57:55,329 --> 00:57:57,468
Will you save me then?

1626
00:57:57,469 --> 00:58:00,139
I think you are a star player.

1627
00:58:00,639 --> 00:58:03,709
I like how you are telling me that.

1628
00:58:03,969 --> 00:58:05,809
You can just stay put.

1629
00:58:05,939 --> 00:58:07,939
I'll feed you and put you to sleep.

1630
00:58:08,239 --> 00:58:09,409
Why would you...

1631
00:58:09,579 --> 00:58:13,118
Why would you hang out with weird guys?

1632
00:58:13,119 --> 00:58:14,119
(Laughing)

1633
00:58:14,120 --> 00:58:15,489
So what are they doing now?

1634
00:58:15,589 --> 00:58:17,819
- They're all sleeping outside.
- That's right.

1635
00:58:17,849 --> 00:58:20,518
What good did pointing fingers do?

1636
00:58:20,519 --> 00:58:21,519
(It all meant nothing.)

1637
00:58:21,520 --> 00:58:23,788
I beat them all.

1638
00:58:23,789 --> 00:58:24,888
You're right.

1639
00:58:24,889 --> 00:58:26,658
They can never come inside.

1640
00:58:26,659 --> 00:58:27,928
(An untouchable threshold)

1641
00:58:27,929 --> 00:58:30,369
They can't cross this threshold.

1642
00:58:30,769 --> 00:58:33,539
I’m starting to change my mind.

1643
00:58:34,139 --> 00:58:37,009
I’m easily swayed.

1644
00:58:37,569 --> 00:58:39,778
I just feel bad for you.

1645
00:58:39,779 --> 00:58:41,478
(I truly feel bad for you.)

1646
00:58:41,479 --> 00:58:43,709
I’m counting on you tomorrow.

1647
00:58:44,279 --> 00:58:46,249
Don't worry and sleep tight.

1648
00:58:46,619 --> 00:58:49,048
- Just do as I say tomorrow.
- Okay.

1649
00:58:49,049 --> 00:58:50,289
(Joon fell for DinDin's trick.)

1650
00:58:50,619 --> 00:58:51,888
(What's happening to the team that's sleeping outdoors?)

1651
00:58:51,889 --> 00:58:53,889
How long do we have to sleep outside?

1652
00:58:54,419 --> 00:58:57,489
This tent is perfect for two.

1653
00:58:58,359 --> 00:59:00,159
It's a bit too small for three.

1654
00:59:00,859 --> 00:59:02,298
I couldn't get DinDin again.

1655
00:59:02,299 --> 00:59:03,499
(I couldn't get DinDin again.)

1656
00:59:03,669 --> 00:59:05,339
He keeps getting us.

1657
00:59:05,499 --> 00:59:08,639
I should have brought him here.

1658
00:59:09,209 --> 00:59:11,138
We all were supposed to sleep together if you weren't caught.

1659
00:59:11,139 --> 00:59:12,408
In this small tent.

1660
00:59:12,409 --> 00:59:13,709
He's right.

1661
00:59:13,779 --> 00:59:16,509
We have to ace tomorrow's mission.

1662
00:59:16,809 --> 00:59:19,019
What's with getting up at 8:12am?

1663
00:59:19,419 --> 00:59:21,718
I know. The hours are very iffy.

1664
00:59:21,719 --> 00:59:22,819
I have no clue.

1665
00:59:23,849 --> 00:59:26,388
- I can't predict a thing.
- I know.

1666
00:59:26,389 --> 00:59:27,465
(They can't predict a thing.)

1667
00:59:27,489 --> 00:59:29,659
I will win tomorrow no matter what.

1668
00:59:30,829 --> 00:59:31,959
We will have our revenge.

1669
00:59:32,899 --> 00:59:35,468
- Let's get back at DinDin.
- Get back at DinDin.

1670
00:59:35,469 --> 00:59:36,469
(We'll get back at DinDin.)

1671
00:59:36,470 --> 00:59:38,739
Let's do our best tomorrow.

1672
00:59:39,339 --> 00:59:40,469
Let's go.

1673
00:59:40,739 --> 00:59:41,869
Good night.

1674
00:59:43,039 --> 00:59:45,508
(Full of questions, )

1675
00:59:45,509 --> 00:59:47,609
(the night has passed.)

1676
00:59:48,079 --> 00:59:51,648
(Morning has come.)

1677
00:59:51,649 --> 00:59:54,478
(Current time, 8:10am)

1678
00:59:54,479 --> 00:59:57,188
(Current time, 8:11am)

1679
00:59:57,189 --> 00:59:58,718
(Current time, 8:12am)

1680
00:59:58,719 --> 01:00:01,259
(The wake-up song is on.)

1681
01:00:02,829 --> 01:00:03,829
Let's go!

1682
01:00:05,129 --> 01:00:06,558
(Waking up at the speed of light)

1683
01:00:06,559 --> 01:00:07,559
Let's go, DinDin.

1684
01:00:07,560 --> 01:00:08,880
(Waking up at the speed of light)

1685
01:00:09,169 --> 01:00:12,569
(Joon, a light sleeper, wakes up as the first one.)

1686
01:00:15,509 --> 01:00:18,309
(The ones who slept outside all got up as well.)

1687
01:00:18,709 --> 01:00:21,279
(The panel placed right in front)

1688
01:00:21,439 --> 01:00:22,479
(Sighing)

1689
01:00:22,749 --> 01:00:24,749
(A morning mission that makes him groan)

1690
01:00:25,079 --> 01:00:27,118
(This is today's morning mission.)

1691
01:00:27,119 --> 01:00:30,149
(Ring the bell at 8:50am.)

1692
01:00:30,549 --> 01:00:33,289
(It's hard to ring the bell at 8:50am sharp.)

1693
01:00:33,859 --> 01:00:37,289
(It will be decided by proximity.)

1694
01:00:38,529 --> 01:00:40,999
(1st and 2nd places will get to have breakfast.)

1695
01:00:41,299 --> 01:00:44,169
(The last three will be assigned with extra work.)

1696
01:00:44,269 --> 01:00:47,469
(Do you remember what happened last night?)

1697
01:00:48,809 --> 01:00:55,079
(They’ve been stripped of anything related to time.)

1698
01:00:55,479 --> 01:00:58,779
(So they don't know what time it is right now.)

1699
01:00:59,219 --> 01:01:02,389
(They can't know the time now. Who will be closest to 8:50am?)

1700
01:01:02,489 --> 01:01:03,689
How would I know the time?

1701
01:01:04,189 --> 01:01:05,989
Ring the bell at 8:50am?

1702
01:01:06,319 --> 01:01:07,999
What time did the bell ring to wake us up?

1703
01:01:08,319 --> 01:01:09,959
Is it 8:12am now?

1704
01:01:12,799 --> 01:01:15,258
(They gave them the hint last night.)

1705
01:01:15,259 --> 01:01:17,369
(The morning song plays at 8:12am.)

1706
01:01:18,429 --> 01:01:19,839
It played at 8:12am.

1707
01:01:20,339 --> 01:01:22,208
So I can ring the bell after 40 minutes.

1708
01:01:22,209 --> 01:01:24,738
We have to ring it after 38 minutes.

1709
01:01:24,739 --> 01:01:25,938
- Right, 38 minutes.
- Yes.

1710
01:01:25,939 --> 01:01:27,138
That's right.

1711
01:01:27,139 --> 01:01:29,549
You will find some hints...

1712
01:01:30,009 --> 01:01:31,109
all over the base camp.

1713
01:01:31,379 --> 01:01:32,548
- Hints?
- Yes.

1714
01:01:32,549 --> 01:01:34,378
- You can look for them.
- All right.

1715
01:01:34,379 --> 01:01:36,389
(Look for the hints and get close to 8:50am.)

1716
01:01:37,549 --> 01:01:38,788
Should I take a guess?

1717
01:01:38,789 --> 01:01:39,819
(Glancing)

1718
01:01:40,019 --> 01:01:41,158
What is this?

1719
01:01:41,159 --> 01:01:43,459
(Hint 1 that DinDin found: Hourglass)

1720
01:01:43,789 --> 01:01:44,888
It's an hourglass.

1721
01:01:44,889 --> 01:01:46,828
(DinDin quickly grabs the hourglass.)

1722
01:01:46,829 --> 01:01:47,928
Give me one.

1723
01:01:47,929 --> 01:01:50,228
(Give me one of those.)

1724
01:01:50,229 --> 01:01:51,549
How many minutes does this count?

1725
01:01:51,729 --> 01:01:52,799
Will you tell me?

1726
01:01:54,499 --> 01:01:56,179
- It says on top.
- You can see it on top.

1727
01:01:57,139 --> 01:01:58,838
It says those minutes.

1728
01:01:58,839 --> 01:02:00,408
(DinDin has a 5-minute hourglass.)

1729
01:02:00,409 --> 01:02:02,609
(Jong Min has a 3-minute hourglass.)

1730
01:02:02,709 --> 01:02:04,779
(Oh, it's written here.)

1731
01:02:06,019 --> 01:02:07,748
(Se Yoon and Seon Ho entered...)

1732
01:02:07,749 --> 01:02:10,419
(the TV room.)

1733
01:02:11,219 --> 01:02:12,418
They blocked the TV too.

1734
01:02:12,419 --> 01:02:13,419
(They can only see the center of the screen.)

1735
01:02:13,420 --> 01:02:15,259
- They blocked the corners?
- Right.

1736
01:02:16,729 --> 01:02:17,928
What is this?

1737
01:02:17,929 --> 01:02:19,458
(The program schedule sitting in front of the TV)

1738
01:02:19,459 --> 01:02:20,529
I see something here.

1739
01:02:21,929 --> 01:02:24,398
(Hint 2: TV Program)

1740
01:02:24,399 --> 01:02:26,239
It's been a while. Tune in "North Windows."

1741
01:02:26,339 --> 01:02:27,638
Look at this.

1742
01:02:27,639 --> 01:02:31,539
(Let me turn it on.)

1743
01:02:34,679 --> 01:02:35,679
(We can't even use the remote control.)

1744
01:02:35,680 --> 01:02:36,709
What's on right now?

1745
01:02:37,409 --> 01:02:39,478
(Meanwhile, in the front yard...)

1746
01:02:39,479 --> 01:02:41,478
Will you do as I say?

1747
01:02:41,479 --> 01:02:42,589
Yes.

1748
01:02:42,749 --> 01:02:44,719
You hit the bell after I ring.

1749
01:02:45,619 --> 01:02:46,958
Don't do anything stupid.

1750
01:02:46,959 --> 01:02:48,859
(Joon joined Team DinDin.)

1751
01:02:54,399 --> 01:02:55,499
What?

1752
01:02:55,599 --> 01:02:56,629
It's a stomach clock.

1753
01:02:56,869 --> 01:02:58,028
I heard the stomach clock.

1754
01:02:58,029 --> 01:03:00,169
So it rings every few minutes.

1755
01:03:01,299 --> 01:03:02,638
So the stomach clock rings.

1756
01:03:02,639 --> 01:03:04,709
(Will it ring every few minutes as they predict?)

1757
01:03:05,039 --> 01:03:06,478
The stomach clock just rang.

1758
01:03:06,479 --> 01:03:08,578
(And there is another hint.)

1759
01:03:08,579 --> 01:03:10,848
(Hint 4: DIY Sundial)

1760
01:03:10,849 --> 01:03:12,379
- Is it a sundial?
- Yes.

1761
01:03:13,679 --> 01:03:17,389
(Jong Min's working on the sundial.)

1762
01:03:17,719 --> 01:03:20,519
Oh, gosh. It worked.

1763
01:03:21,719 --> 01:03:24,589
(He completed the sundial.)

1764
01:03:25,059 --> 01:03:28,758
(Now he just has to read it.)

1765
01:03:28,759 --> 01:03:29,798
How do I read this?

1766
01:03:29,799 --> 01:03:32,129
(He doesn't know how to read it.)

1767
01:03:32,869 --> 01:03:33,938
What are you doing?

1768
01:03:33,939 --> 01:03:34,939
(They found the hint. But they don't know how to use it.)

1769
01:03:34,940 --> 01:03:36,139
You don't know how to use it.

1770
01:03:37,139 --> 01:03:38,309
I'm studying it.

1771
01:03:38,639 --> 01:03:40,879
- You can't study it.
- Of course, I can.

1772
01:03:41,009 --> 01:03:42,039
All right.

1773
01:03:42,509 --> 01:03:44,448
This is how I'm going to work it out.

1774
01:03:44,449 --> 01:03:45,449
(DinDin's way of time deduction)

1775
01:03:45,450 --> 01:03:47,149
This is being recorded.

1776
01:03:48,879 --> 01:03:51,088
(Hint 5: The microphone's recording time)

1777
01:03:51,089 --> 01:03:53,359
(Even the production crew didn't know about this.)

1778
01:03:54,159 --> 01:03:57,989
(The recorder unit connected to the microphone)

1779
01:03:59,899 --> 01:04:02,629
- Five minutes are over.
- What?

1780
01:04:03,329 --> 01:04:05,229
So it has been 26 minutes.

1781
01:04:05,599 --> 01:04:08,669
It has been 26 minutes.

1782
01:04:08,969 --> 01:04:10,369
It has been 26 minutes.

1783
01:04:10,539 --> 01:04:12,708
So it has been 26 minutes.

1784
01:04:12,709 --> 01:04:13,738
(The hints are getting up at 8:12am and an hourglass of 5 minutes.)

1785
01:04:13,739 --> 01:04:14,979
That's 26 minutes...

1786
01:04:15,679 --> 01:04:18,208
(And the time recorded on the recording unit)

1787
01:04:18,209 --> 01:04:20,625
So I can just ring the bell when it hits 1 hour and 2 minutes.

1788
01:04:20,649 --> 01:04:21,679
Do you understand?

1789
01:04:23,149 --> 01:04:24,149
Did you get it?

1790
01:04:24,150 --> 01:04:25,895
(He nodded. But it looks like he didn't get DinDin.)

1791
01:04:25,919 --> 01:04:28,388
- So this counts five minutes.
- Yes.

1792
01:04:28,389 --> 01:04:29,458
(DinDin's deduction lecture)

1793
01:04:29,459 --> 01:04:33,158
- They woke us up at 8:12am.
- Right.

1794
01:04:33,159 --> 01:04:34,258
Then we got out.

1795
01:04:34,259 --> 01:04:35,328
(Morning song played at 8:12am)

1796
01:04:35,329 --> 01:04:36,398
We heard the song.

1797
01:04:36,399 --> 01:04:39,198
Then I flipped the hourglass.

1798
01:04:39,199 --> 01:04:41,469
That's about when two minutes have passed.

1799
01:04:41,699 --> 01:04:43,839
- That must have been 8:14am.
- Right.

1800
01:04:44,069 --> 01:04:45,708
Then another five minutes have passed.

1801
01:04:45,709 --> 01:04:47,738
- So it's about 8:19am.
- Right.

1802
01:04:47,739 --> 01:04:49,139
(DinDin estimates it to be 8:19am.)

1803
01:04:49,279 --> 01:04:51,979
(It's exactly 8:19am.)

1804
01:04:52,319 --> 01:04:55,619
We can ring the bell about 31 minutes later.

1805
01:04:56,119 --> 01:04:58,119
Add 31 minutes and 26 minutes.

1806
01:04:58,619 --> 01:05:02,059
You can hit the bell when it hits 57 minutes.

1807
01:05:02,389 --> 01:05:04,459
- Okay, 57 minutes.
- Right.

1808
01:05:04,989 --> 01:05:06,858
(Reading the production crew's face)

1809
01:05:06,859 --> 01:05:08,158
- Did you see that?
- You are a genius.

1810
01:05:08,159 --> 01:05:10,098
Did you see that?

1811
01:05:10,099 --> 01:05:12,368
(He starts showing off right away.)

1812
01:05:12,369 --> 01:05:13,739
Go and check around.

1813
01:05:14,469 --> 01:05:15,569
You are a genius.

1814
01:05:15,669 --> 01:05:18,669
Stomach clock? They are setting them up.

1815
01:05:19,109 --> 01:05:21,679
You have to think beyond that.

1816
01:05:23,349 --> 01:05:24,349
(The stomach clock's ringing again.)

1817
01:05:24,350 --> 01:05:25,478
They prepared all those things.

1818
01:05:25,479 --> 01:05:28,018
I have my own logic set up.

1819
01:05:28,019 --> 01:05:30,589
No matter how much they prepared to set me up,

1820
01:05:31,249 --> 01:05:32,858
I just check it out. That's all.

1821
01:05:32,859 --> 01:05:34,395
(I don't care what the production crew has prepared.)

1822
01:05:34,419 --> 01:05:36,788
(Jong Min starts assembling the sundial again.)

1823
01:05:36,789 --> 01:05:37,989
What do you think of this?

1824
01:05:39,229 --> 01:05:41,058
This is just like yesterday.

1825
01:05:41,059 --> 01:05:43,929
(It means nothing.)

1826
01:05:44,399 --> 01:05:46,398
(Was I like this yesterday?)

1827
01:05:46,399 --> 01:05:47,645
This is how you looked yesterday.

1828
01:05:47,669 --> 01:05:49,169
So you decided to be...

1829
01:05:49,769 --> 01:05:51,308
DinDin's minion?

1830
01:05:51,309 --> 01:05:52,908
(You decided to become DinDin's minion.)

1831
01:05:52,909 --> 01:05:54,838
- Joon.
- Don't listen to him.

1832
01:05:54,839 --> 01:05:56,548
- Come here.
- Live your life to the fullest.

1833
01:05:56,549 --> 01:05:58,109
We all live different lives.

1834
01:05:58,279 --> 01:06:00,179
All right. You can flatter him.

1835
01:06:01,019 --> 01:06:02,219
You can go.

1836
01:06:02,749 --> 01:06:04,148
Be the tail of a rat.

1837
01:06:04,149 --> 01:06:05,318
(Team DinDin: Rat and Rat's tail)

1838
01:06:05,319 --> 01:06:08,019
You can be the tail of a rat.

1839
01:06:08,859 --> 01:06:11,858
Channel Eight has a documentary on.

1840
01:06:11,859 --> 01:06:13,959
Other channels don't have anything on.

1841
01:06:14,399 --> 01:06:16,368
- "The Return of Superman?"
- "The Return of Superman."

1842
01:06:16,369 --> 01:06:18,049
(Let me turn on "The Return of Superman.")

1843
01:06:19,739 --> 01:06:21,999
- I can't even talk to you.
- You're right.

1844
01:06:22,569 --> 01:06:25,208
You can turn the channel here.

1845
01:06:25,209 --> 01:06:27,338
What do you mean other channels don't work?

1846
01:06:27,339 --> 01:06:28,638
Se Yoon told me it didn't work.

1847
01:06:28,639 --> 01:06:31,609
- Gosh, this is so frustrating.
- Seon Ho, you are frustrating.

1848
01:06:31,879 --> 01:06:33,778
I'm not showing off or anything.

1849
01:06:33,779 --> 01:06:36,048
These guys are so stupid.

1850
01:06:36,049 --> 01:06:38,649
DinDin, we'll check your microphone.

1851
01:06:38,819 --> 01:06:39,819
Why?

1852
01:06:40,059 --> 01:06:41,907
- We got a tip-off.
- What tip-off?

1853
01:06:42,003 --> 01:06:44,112
We're going to check your mic, Im Cheol.

1854
01:06:44,292 --> 01:06:45,292
Why?

1855
01:06:45,401 --> 01:06:46,730
We got a tip-off.

1856
01:06:46,731 --> 01:06:47,830
What tip-off?

1857
01:06:47,831 --> 01:06:49,200
Let us just check your mic.

1858
01:06:49,201 --> 01:06:50,201
We're doomed.

1859
01:06:50,371 --> 01:06:51,971
Is it still possible?

1860
01:06:53,271 --> 01:06:54,271
Is this okay?

1861
01:06:54,272 --> 01:06:55,280
(He tries to run away.)

1862
01:06:55,281 --> 01:06:57,341
What? Why are you doing this?

1863
01:06:57,711 --> 01:06:58,880
It doesn't have the time.

1864
01:06:58,881 --> 01:07:00,057
(But the escape attempt fails.)

1865
01:07:00,081 --> 01:07:01,280
I trusted him.

1866
01:07:01,281 --> 01:07:02,420
(I was only relying on DinDin... What do I do now?)

1867
01:07:02,421 --> 01:07:03,451
What do I do?

1868
01:07:04,281 --> 01:07:05,791
Bring that here.

1869
01:07:05,821 --> 01:07:07,191
That one.

1870
01:07:07,521 --> 01:07:09,021
The hourglass.

1871
01:07:10,321 --> 01:07:12,961
(Running)

1872
01:07:13,191 --> 01:07:14,391
Where are you going, Rat Tail?

1873
01:07:15,201 --> 01:07:16,660
Where are you going, Rat Tail?

1874
01:07:16,661 --> 01:07:18,130
- He wants you to bring that?
- I'm running an errand.

1875
01:07:18,131 --> 01:07:19,401
He wants you to bring that?

1876
01:07:19,671 --> 01:07:21,441
Come here.

1877
01:07:21,771 --> 01:07:23,100
I have to get back quickly.

1878
01:07:23,101 --> 01:07:24,841
Just come here.

1879
01:07:25,011 --> 01:07:26,941
Take this as well. He'll like it. Hey!

1880
01:07:27,471 --> 01:07:30,380
If you just do one when told to do one, you won't be loved.

1881
01:07:30,381 --> 01:07:31,450
- Take this.
- Okay.

1882
01:07:31,451 --> 01:07:33,310
And don't wear your cap so straight.

1883
01:07:33,311 --> 01:07:35,021
You should wear it like this.

1884
01:07:35,421 --> 01:07:36,451
Get back there.

1885
01:07:36,651 --> 01:07:37,851
Live diligently.

1886
01:07:38,351 --> 01:07:40,350
Drink some water too.

1887
01:07:40,351 --> 01:07:42,121
Thank you.

1888
01:07:42,761 --> 01:07:43,890
After that...

1889
01:07:43,891 --> 01:07:45,030
(They need to find another method now...)

1890
01:07:45,031 --> 01:07:47,861
From 33... Then 35 minutes...

1891
01:07:47,961 --> 01:07:49,200
It was 33 minutes earlier.

1892
01:07:49,201 --> 01:07:50,531
It was at 33 minutes earlier.

1893
01:07:51,631 --> 01:07:55,241
(He continues to figure out a way.)

1894
01:07:56,101 --> 01:07:59,170
(Calculating)

1895
01:07:59,171 --> 01:08:02,411
(Calculation complete)

1896
01:08:03,411 --> 01:08:07,811
(Noting the elapsed time on the hourglass)

1897
01:08:08,621 --> 01:08:13,221
(Then he quietly leaves to look for other clues.)

1898
01:08:13,651 --> 01:08:15,961
(Seon Ho is only focusing on the TV.)

1899
01:08:17,261 --> 01:08:18,630
If someone rings this,

1900
01:08:18,631 --> 01:08:19,830
(These two are still lost.)

1901
01:08:19,831 --> 01:08:21,261
will it tell the time?

1902
01:08:22,061 --> 01:08:24,971
- The sun didn't...
- A single honk of the horn...

1903
01:08:25,671 --> 01:08:27,730
- That's one second.
- We should turn the lights off.

1904
01:08:27,731 --> 01:08:28,741
Eight.

1905
01:08:29,001 --> 01:08:30,561
Because of the lighting, the sundial...

1906
01:08:31,171 --> 01:08:32,470
That's been in the way.

1907
01:08:32,471 --> 01:08:34,371
It would run the same way with the lighting.

1908
01:08:34,711 --> 01:08:37,210
The sun is right there.

1909
01:08:37,211 --> 01:08:39,211
It's the same thing.

1910
01:08:39,411 --> 01:08:41,051
It's not working because of the lighting.

1911
01:08:42,721 --> 01:08:43,980
I should take it under the sun.

1912
01:08:43,981 --> 01:08:45,721
(Moving to a place with sunlight)

1913
01:08:47,491 --> 01:08:49,821
(Se Yoon's shadow)

1914
01:08:50,021 --> 01:08:52,930
(Blocking the sunlight with his body)

1915
01:08:52,931 --> 01:08:54,231
Go away!

1916
01:08:54,431 --> 01:08:55,431
You know what?

1917
01:08:55,661 --> 01:08:58,001
I'm not confident I can do this mission well today.

1918
01:08:58,631 --> 01:09:00,270
Let me just do it once.

1919
01:09:00,271 --> 01:09:01,817
(Let's just give up together, Jong Min.)

1920
01:09:01,841 --> 01:09:02,940
Come on.

1921
01:09:02,941 --> 01:09:04,640
I won't be able to go home today.

1922
01:09:04,641 --> 01:09:06,347
(But Jong Min has no intention of giving up.)

1923
01:09:06,371 --> 01:09:08,881
(He's not falling for it.)

1924
01:09:09,241 --> 01:09:11,381
(Should I also look for clues?)

1925
01:09:11,551 --> 01:09:13,950
(The stomach clock goes off again.)

1926
01:09:13,951 --> 01:09:16,050
That's the fourth time.

1927
01:09:16,051 --> 01:09:17,420
(The stomach clock went off 4 times so far.)

1928
01:09:17,421 --> 01:09:19,650
Stomach clock, four times.

1929
01:09:19,651 --> 01:09:21,350
(At which interval does the stomach clock go off?)

1930
01:09:21,351 --> 01:09:22,691
It went off four times?

1931
01:09:23,221 --> 01:09:25,190
The stomach clock? Four times.

1932
01:09:25,191 --> 01:09:27,031
(He can't really tell yet.)

1933
01:09:27,361 --> 01:09:29,661
There's something... Are there hints at the back too?

1934
01:09:30,101 --> 01:09:31,161
No?

1935
01:09:32,471 --> 01:09:34,501
Why did they tell us to ring it at 8:50am?

1936
01:09:35,571 --> 01:09:36,770
It could have been 9am.

1937
01:09:36,771 --> 01:09:37,800
(Ring the bell at exactly 8:50am. The 2 people who get closest...)

1938
01:09:37,801 --> 01:09:39,881
(win breakfast! Everyone else has to do extra work.)

1939
01:09:40,171 --> 01:09:41,881
Why 8:50am?

1940
01:09:42,711 --> 01:09:45,181
Why not 9am? Koreans like exact times.

1941
01:09:45,251 --> 01:09:48,080
That's just useless, Mister.

1942
01:09:48,081 --> 01:09:49,250
Why 8:50am?

1943
01:09:49,251 --> 01:09:50,521
(Feeling frustrated)

1944
01:09:50,621 --> 01:09:52,621
They said the answer lied in the problem.

1945
01:09:52,751 --> 01:09:54,521
- Carry on.
- Okay.

1946
01:09:55,161 --> 01:09:57,791
Why did they wake us up at 8:12am?

1947
01:09:57,991 --> 01:10:00,031
(Ignoring him)

1948
01:10:00,761 --> 01:10:02,061
Eight, one, two.

1949
01:10:03,431 --> 01:10:04,431
(Rumbling)

1950
01:10:05,901 --> 01:10:07,607
It growled again. How many times has it gone off now?

1951
01:10:07,631 --> 01:10:08,671
The fourth time?

1952
01:10:09,941 --> 01:10:11,001
(Rumbling)

1953
01:10:13,441 --> 01:10:15,511
What's that rumbling noise?

1954
01:10:17,211 --> 01:10:19,651
(That moment)

1955
01:10:19,951 --> 01:10:23,220
Coming up next, "Boss in the Mirror."

1956
01:10:23,221 --> 01:10:24,657
("Boss in the Mirror" is coming up next!)

1957
01:10:24,681 --> 01:10:26,351
That's right. It should come up soon.

1958
01:10:27,651 --> 01:10:30,221
(That means...)

1959
01:10:30,991 --> 01:10:32,230
(They're currently here.)

1960
01:10:32,231 --> 01:10:34,431
(It's just before 8:40am)

1961
01:10:35,001 --> 01:10:36,801
It will soon be 8:40am.

1962
01:10:37,861 --> 01:10:40,401
(Seon Ho seems to be betting everything on the TV schedule.)

1963
01:10:41,001 --> 01:10:43,741
(Meanwhile, DinDin is looking for another way after losing the mic.)

1964
01:10:44,671 --> 01:10:46,111
Listen to me.

1965
01:10:46,811 --> 01:10:47,911
Let's close the door.

1966
01:10:49,811 --> 01:10:52,851
(What is he trying to say that he needs to close the door?)

1967
01:10:53,381 --> 01:10:55,451
This camera is filming us now.

1968
01:10:56,581 --> 01:10:58,651
If I just turn this off for a bit...

1969
01:10:59,421 --> 01:11:01,251
and press menu,

1970
01:11:02,821 --> 01:11:04,090
(Menu)

1971
01:11:04,091 --> 01:11:05,391
In the settings,

1972
01:11:05,791 --> 01:11:08,601
(He can check out the current time!)

1973
01:11:09,231 --> 01:11:10,961
you can check out the date and time.

1974
01:11:11,431 --> 01:11:13,271
But it's filming right now.

1975
01:11:14,031 --> 01:11:15,641
What happens if I turn it off for a bit?

1976
01:11:17,001 --> 01:11:18,370
One, two, three.

1977
01:11:18,371 --> 01:11:20,740
(Giving up his one-shot chance to get a hint)

1978
01:11:20,741 --> 01:11:21,741
It worked.

1979
01:11:21,742 --> 01:11:23,141
(It worked!)

1980
01:11:23,981 --> 01:11:25,211
(Date and time)

1981
01:11:29,021 --> 01:11:31,751
(Current time: 8:37am?)

1982
01:11:33,251 --> 01:11:37,321
(He quickly writes it down on the hourglass!)

1983
01:11:37,891 --> 01:11:39,761
Wasn't that amazing?

1984
01:11:40,261 --> 01:11:44,461
Why not? You said the hints are hidden in various places.

1985
01:11:45,771 --> 01:11:49,171
(Meanwhile, Joon is in the front yard.)

1986
01:11:51,741 --> 01:11:56,041
(He suddenly heads somewhere.)

1987
01:11:57,411 --> 01:12:00,481
(He checks the camera.)

1988
01:12:00,981 --> 01:12:03,281
(Then...)

1989
01:12:04,881 --> 01:12:07,551
(Is he using the same method as DinDin?)

1990
01:12:08,191 --> 01:12:10,561
(Checking the time)

1991
01:12:12,161 --> 01:12:13,631
It was 8:12am earlier, right?

1992
01:12:13,731 --> 01:12:16,530
So in 38 minutes,

1993
01:12:16,531 --> 01:12:17,930
it will be 50 minutes.

1994
01:12:17,931 --> 01:12:19,491
(Lee Joon also knows the current time!)

1995
01:12:19,601 --> 01:12:22,100
It feels like we did this briefly, but a lot of time has passed.

1996
01:12:22,101 --> 01:12:23,241
Where's Im Cheol?

1997
01:12:24,641 --> 01:12:26,787
- I've figured something out.
- What did you figure out?

1998
01:12:26,811 --> 01:12:28,580
You're catching up well.

1999
01:12:28,581 --> 01:12:29,901
You're talking about that, right?

2000
01:12:30,081 --> 01:12:31,881
- Pausing the camera...
- I checked the time.

2001
01:12:32,251 --> 01:12:33,311
What was the time?

2002
01:12:33,611 --> 01:12:35,550
I checked it when it was 8:49am.

2003
01:12:35,551 --> 01:12:36,551
I mean 8:39am.

2004
01:12:37,181 --> 01:12:38,350
- That's right.
- Is it?

2005
01:12:38,351 --> 01:12:40,120
- Then it's accurate.
- It's accurate.

2006
01:12:40,121 --> 01:12:42,390
- Then it's 8:39am now.
- Right.

2007
01:12:42,391 --> 01:12:44,660
Then, it's 39...

2008
01:12:44,661 --> 01:12:47,831
The last time I checked, it was 8:39am, and I turned this.

2009
01:12:48,261 --> 01:12:50,030
- Then...
- I got the same calculation too.

2010
01:12:50,031 --> 01:12:51,530
Eleven minutes... Joon.

2011
01:12:51,531 --> 01:12:53,501
- You improve when you're with me.
- Right.

2012
01:12:53,531 --> 01:12:56,270
If you're with them, you'll say, "The 50 minutes will have meaning."

2013
01:12:56,271 --> 01:12:58,171
The 50 minutes has no meaning.

2014
01:13:00,171 --> 01:13:01,941
Why isn't "Boss in the Mirror" starting?

2015
01:13:02,711 --> 01:13:04,180
That means it's all wrong.

2016
01:13:04,181 --> 01:13:05,681
There's no point in watching this.

2017
01:13:10,221 --> 01:13:14,351
Why don't TV programs air exactly according to the schedule?

2018
01:13:15,021 --> 01:13:16,660
They say it starts at 40 minutes,

2019
01:13:16,661 --> 01:13:18,461
but then there is a few minute delay.

2020
01:13:18,991 --> 01:13:20,561
What is the reason?

2021
01:13:21,661 --> 01:13:23,760
(Due to commercials, the actual start time may differ...)

2022
01:13:23,761 --> 01:13:24,831
(from the schedule.)

2023
01:13:26,101 --> 01:13:28,771
According to the schedule, "Boss in the Mirror" starts at...

2024
01:13:30,201 --> 01:13:32,841
(The stomach clock went off again.)

2025
01:13:33,571 --> 01:13:36,311
(Did Se Yoon notice something?)

2026
01:13:37,341 --> 01:13:39,087
- It's...
- Let's assume the stomach clock...

2027
01:13:39,111 --> 01:13:40,951
rings every five minutes.

2028
01:13:41,181 --> 01:13:43,251
It rang six times now.

2029
01:13:43,351 --> 01:13:44,650
That's 30 minutes.

2030
01:13:44,651 --> 01:13:47,491
That means it's 8:42am now.

2031
01:13:47,591 --> 01:13:50,291
It fits perfectly because "Boss in the Mirror" isn't on yet.

2032
01:13:51,991 --> 01:13:52,991
What?

2033
01:13:53,891 --> 01:13:55,131
Are you looking for this?

2034
01:13:56,331 --> 01:13:57,900
- Are you looking for this?
- Come on.

2035
01:13:57,901 --> 01:13:59,701
You won't get it so easily.

2036
01:14:00,301 --> 01:14:02,341
I can't let you go home alone.

2037
01:14:02,941 --> 01:14:04,941
Just take a guess.

2038
01:14:06,041 --> 01:14:08,371
(Touching)

2039
01:14:09,041 --> 01:14:11,780
(Meanwhile, Jong Min bet everything on the hourglass and sundial.)

2040
01:14:11,781 --> 01:14:12,951
The lighting...

2041
