2293
01:23:35,541 --> 01:23:36,640
No. They aren't out yet.

2294
01:23:36,641 --> 01:23:37,941
I saw the pear blossoms.

2295
01:23:38,781 --> 01:23:42,110
Let's head to the pear farm to help out with the farm work.

2296
01:23:42,111 --> 01:23:43,750
- Okay!
- Thank you.

2297
01:23:43,751 --> 01:23:44,820
(Let's get going now.)

2298
01:23:44,821 --> 01:23:46,701
We have up to 100 dollars. What should we have?

2299
01:23:47,851 --> 01:23:48,891
This is amazing.

2300
01:23:49,161 --> 01:23:51,360
What should we have? This is amazing!

2301
01:23:51,361 --> 01:23:53,137
(Let's go and eat before the stomach clock goes off!)

2302
01:23:53,161 --> 01:23:54,531
I'm not really an assistant.

2303
01:23:54,961 --> 01:23:56,001
We had a meeting together.

2304
01:23:56,461 --> 01:23:57,530
That was it.

2305
01:23:57,531 --> 01:23:59,270
He wasn't an assistant. We had a meeting together.

2306
01:23:59,271 --> 01:24:02,030
Right. "This is what I think. What about you?"

2307
01:24:02,031 --> 01:24:03,270
This was what it was like.

2308
01:24:03,271 --> 01:24:05,500
That was it. I wasn't an assistant.

2309
01:24:05,501 --> 01:24:09,040
I think you'll be called the rat tail on the show.

2310
01:24:09,041 --> 01:24:10,681
(The rat tail's explanation)

2311
01:24:10,881 --> 01:24:12,041
What should we have?

2312
01:24:12,881 --> 01:24:14,851
I'm not sure. We weren't told about anything.

2313
01:24:15,451 --> 01:24:16,880
- I'm sure it'll be something good.
- I don't know.

2314
01:24:16,881 --> 01:24:18,921
(They set off while being curious about the menu.)

2315
01:24:19,921 --> 01:24:22,321
I feel really happy that we are able to eat,

2316
01:24:23,461 --> 01:24:25,620
but I feel delighted that we won against DinDin.

2317
01:24:25,621 --> 01:24:27,791
Oh, come on. When did we ever lose to him?

2318
01:24:29,161 --> 01:24:30,281
We lost to him all the time.

2319
01:24:31,361 --> 01:24:33,001
Let's enjoy a nice meal...

2320
01:24:33,301 --> 01:24:35,841
- And head home.
- and head home.

2321
01:24:36,341 --> 01:24:37,840
We're here. Where is this?

2322
01:24:37,841 --> 01:24:40,841
(They arrive at their destination in just 5 minutes.)

2323
01:24:41,511 --> 01:24:46,251
(A place filled with delicious smells...)

2324
01:24:47,111 --> 01:24:49,981
(and different types of food)

2325
01:24:50,251 --> 01:24:52,020
We're at the market.

2326
01:24:52,021 --> 01:24:54,821
Right. This is Naju Moksagoeul Market.

2327
01:24:55,521 --> 01:24:57,760
You can eat freely with the coupons you received.

2328
01:24:57,761 --> 01:24:59,160
- We can eat freely?
- We can eat freely?

2329
01:24:59,161 --> 01:25:00,960
- Yes.
- We can spend all 100 dollars?

2330
01:25:00,961 --> 01:25:01,991
Of course.

2331
01:25:02,361 --> 01:25:04,400
- Where should we go first?
- Shall we look around?

2332
01:25:04,401 --> 01:25:06,230
Let's move in and take a look.

2333
01:25:06,231 --> 01:25:07,400
- The market?
- Yes.

2334
01:25:07,401 --> 01:25:09,347
- We can eat in the market?
- There are many interesting places.

2335
01:25:09,371 --> 01:25:10,501
- Really?
- Really?

2336
01:25:11,041 --> 01:25:13,140
So this is a duck place.

2337
01:25:13,141 --> 01:25:14,441
It's a duck place?

2338
01:25:14,611 --> 01:25:16,211
Duck must be a famous dish here.

2339
01:25:16,641 --> 01:25:19,810
- This place got my attention.
- This dumpling place looks great.

2340
01:25:19,811 --> 01:25:21,310
This place got my attention. The dumplings look great.

2341
01:25:21,311 --> 01:25:23,321
- The steamed buns look good.
- Gosh, dumplings!

2342
01:25:23,781 --> 01:25:24,950
The dumplings look so good!

2343
01:25:24,951 --> 01:25:26,790
Gosh! Hello.

2344
01:25:26,791 --> 01:25:28,091
How much are they? Hello.

2345
01:25:28,691 --> 01:25:29,860
They look delicious.

2346
01:25:29,861 --> 01:25:31,821
(Se Yoon's eyes already look desperate.)

2347
01:25:31,861 --> 01:25:33,837
- There's sundae as well.
- The dumplings look great.

2348
01:25:33,861 --> 01:25:35,190
- Let's go for it.
- Should we go for it?

2349
01:25:35,191 --> 01:25:37,060
Let's have the meat dumplings and kimchi dumplings as an appetizer.

2350
01:25:37,061 --> 01:25:38,660
- Right. I want kimchi dumplings.
- Let's do that.

2351
01:25:38,661 --> 01:25:40,061
There are shrimp dumplings as well.

2352
01:25:40,401 --> 01:25:42,770
Can you walk past a dumpling place?

2353
01:25:42,771 --> 01:25:44,900
- That's impossible.
- When the steam is out,

2354
01:25:44,901 --> 01:25:46,270
you have to have some of them.

2355
01:25:46,271 --> 01:25:47,671
You must have the kimchi dumplings.

2356
01:25:47,871 --> 01:25:48,940
Gosh.

2357
01:25:48,941 --> 01:25:50,040
Wrap the dumplings with the lettuce.

2358
01:25:50,041 --> 01:25:52,241
- Really?
- Dumplings wrapped with lettuce?

2359
01:25:52,281 --> 01:25:54,150
- Dumplings wrapped with lettuce?
- Yes.

2360
01:25:54,151 --> 01:25:55,180
- Yes.
- What is this?

2361
01:25:55,181 --> 01:25:57,421
This is the bite-sized lettuce and dumpling.

2362
01:25:57,851 --> 01:25:59,391
- They're eaten as wraps.
- Like this?

2363
01:25:59,521 --> 01:26:00,750
The dumplings are wrapped with the lettuce?

2364
01:26:00,751 --> 01:26:02,291
- Right.
- This is unique.

2365
01:26:02,521 --> 01:26:04,121
I can't imagine what it will taste like.

2366
01:26:04,821 --> 01:26:08,161
(Making a wrap right away)

2367
01:26:08,531 --> 01:26:10,160
It's my first time trying a dumpling wrap.

2368
01:26:10,161 --> 01:26:12,300
(Seon Ho takes a bite as well.)

2369
01:26:12,301 --> 01:26:14,001
Gosh, a dumpling wrap?

2370
01:26:14,301 --> 01:26:15,630
It's the first time in my life of eating...

2371
01:26:15,631 --> 01:26:17,971
to try a dumpling wrap.

2372
01:26:18,071 --> 01:26:19,351
It doesn't feel awkward, though.

2373
01:26:19,671 --> 01:26:22,371
(It totally suits his taste.)

2374
01:26:23,111 --> 01:26:25,641
(After devouring the last piece, )

2375
01:26:25,781 --> 01:26:26,910
(the 2 plates worth 10 dollars in total were cleared.)

2376
01:26:26,911 --> 01:26:28,750
- We finished them so quickly.
- Right.

2377
01:26:28,751 --> 01:26:29,927
(2 plates worth 10 dollars are devoured in a flash.)

2378
01:26:29,951 --> 01:26:32,021
There are no pears yet. What are we going to do?

2379
01:26:32,121 --> 01:26:33,401
There are no pears on the trees.

2380
01:26:33,921 --> 01:26:36,490
The farm is huge. What are we doing?

2381
01:26:36,491 --> 01:26:37,867
(This is a big pear farm spanning approximately 20,000m².)

2382
01:26:37,891 --> 01:26:40,761
There are no pears in the pear farm. Why are we here?

2383
01:26:41,191 --> 01:26:44,401
You're going to help out at this pear farm now.

2384
01:26:44,831 --> 01:26:47,701
We will bring in the person who will help you work.

2385
01:26:48,101 --> 01:26:49,770
He's here. Hello.

2386
01:26:49,771 --> 01:26:51,101
- Come forward, please.
- Hello.

2387
01:26:51,341 --> 01:26:53,870
(Imposing)

2388
01:26:53,871 --> 01:26:56,180
- Hello.
- He has a strong presence.

2389
01:26:56,181 --> 01:26:57,241
- Hello.
- Hello.

2390
01:26:57,311 --> 01:26:58,380
Nice to meet you.

2391
01:26:58,381 --> 01:27:00,011
You all look handsome.

2392
01:27:00,781 --> 01:27:02,780
- What are we doing?
- You need to do some work.

2393
01:27:02,781 --> 01:27:04,580
But there are no pears here.

2394
01:27:04,581 --> 01:27:05,651
They're in here.

2395
01:27:05,991 --> 01:27:08,190
I see. You must have a lot.

2396
01:27:08,191 --> 01:27:09,920
We're here to get some pears.

2397
01:27:09,921 --> 01:27:12,990
By the way, may I ask how old you are?

2398
01:27:12,991 --> 01:27:14,931
- You seem younger than Jong Min.
- I...

2399
01:27:15,891 --> 01:27:17,430
- You're handsome.
- Really?

2400
01:27:17,431 --> 01:27:18,901
I turned 60 last year.

2401
01:27:18,931 --> 01:27:20,971
- What?
- Seriously?

2402
01:27:21,601 --> 01:27:23,470
- Really?
- Yes.

2403
01:27:23,471 --> 01:27:25,200
You look really young for your age.

2404
01:27:25,201 --> 01:27:26,770
- You look unbelievably young.
- I thought...

2405
01:27:26,771 --> 01:27:28,871
- You look so young.
- Honestly...

2406
01:27:29,171 --> 01:27:30,810
Is it because you eat a lot of pears?

2407
01:27:30,811 --> 01:27:32,510
Exactly. Naju pears are the best.

2408
01:27:32,511 --> 01:27:33,780
Pears are very juicy.

2409
01:27:33,781 --> 01:27:34,810
Your skin is nice, too.

2410
01:27:34,811 --> 01:27:37,020
Naju pears are different?

2411
01:27:37,021 --> 01:27:39,280
- Why are they different?
- Naju pears are famous.

2412
01:27:39,281 --> 01:27:41,650
Naju pears have long benefited...

2413
01:27:41,651 --> 01:27:43,921
from the perfect combination...

2414
01:27:44,261 --> 01:27:45,901
of soil, climate, and natural conditions.

2415
01:27:46,561 --> 01:27:48,891
And nice people like me are growing them.

2416
01:27:49,361 --> 01:27:50,430
Just imagine how great they must be.

2417
01:27:50,431 --> 01:27:52,100
He sounds like DinDin.

2418
01:27:52,101 --> 01:27:53,261
(He sounds just like DinDin.)

2419
01:27:53,431 --> 01:27:55,330
But there are no pears yet.

2420
01:27:55,331 --> 01:27:57,971
- There are only flowers.
- We should make pears now.

2421
01:27:58,101 --> 01:28:00,370
The pear blossoms are so pretty.

2422
01:28:00,371 --> 01:28:01,771
They look like cherry blossoms.

2423
01:28:01,871 --> 01:28:04,711
We should become bees and transfer the pollen.

2424
01:28:05,081 --> 01:28:06,251
- Bees?
- Handsome bees.

2425
01:28:06,781 --> 01:28:09,451
We're going to get pollen on the blossoms to pollinate them.

2426
01:28:09,551 --> 01:28:11,020
- I see.
- That's what we're doing?

2427
01:28:11,021 --> 01:28:12,661
We're going to play the role of the bees.

2428
01:28:12,721 --> 01:28:15,550
- It will be a delicate task.
- That's right.

2429
01:28:15,551 --> 01:28:17,090
- We're bees.
- Yes.

2430
01:28:17,091 --> 01:28:18,861
We have amazing bees today.

2431
01:28:20,461 --> 01:28:22,391
- Coat the pollen onto the brush.
- Coat it.

2432
01:28:22,831 --> 01:28:24,530
- You see the blossom here?
- Yes.

2433
01:28:24,531 --> 01:28:25,600
Dab it.

2434
01:28:25,601 --> 01:28:27,200
- Just like that?
- Dab it here.

2435
01:28:27,201 --> 01:28:28,570
- That's right.
- Gently.

2436
01:28:28,571 --> 01:28:31,301
It's like applying a blusher.

2437
01:28:31,371 --> 01:28:32,941
Exactly. That's how you do it.

2438
01:28:33,011 --> 01:28:35,640
- I see.
- The pollen falls off the brush,

2439
01:28:35,641 --> 01:28:37,810
and the blossoms are not stressed out.

2440
01:28:37,811 --> 01:28:39,580
- It's simple.
- It is.

2441
01:28:39,581 --> 01:28:41,650
But you must keep your head high up the whole time.

2442
01:28:41,651 --> 01:28:43,221
- It's not easy.
- It's tiring.

2443
01:28:44,151 --> 01:28:46,791
- Can't you just use a drone?
- We do use drones.

2444
01:28:46,891 --> 01:28:48,220
- It'll be quick.
- But it's not accurate.

2445
01:28:48,221 --> 01:28:49,320
- It's not accurate?
- No.

2446
01:28:49,321 --> 01:28:51,191
The handsome bees should do the work now.

2447
01:28:51,921 --> 01:28:53,860
- Stop talking.
- We have a drone engineer here.

2448
01:28:53,861 --> 01:28:55,291
I've already tried it.

2449
01:28:55,731 --> 01:28:58,131
Start from here, and don't miss a single blossom. Look.

2450
01:28:58,931 --> 01:29:00,300
I forgot to apply sunscreen.

2451
01:29:00,301 --> 01:29:01,901
Me too. Just do it.

2452
01:29:02,431 --> 01:29:04,171
I'm also a celebrity here.

2453
01:29:04,771 --> 01:29:06,771
Let's do the work. Joon is doing well.

2454
01:29:07,541 --> 01:29:09,171
(Dabbing gently)

2455
01:29:09,981 --> 01:29:11,881
(Joon's perfect touch)

2456
01:29:12,881 --> 01:29:14,811
I should join Joon's fan club.

2457
01:29:15,381 --> 01:29:16,381
Thank you.

2458
01:29:17,151 --> 01:29:18,750
Pears grow well...

2459
01:29:18,751 --> 01:29:21,251
only when we put in our best effort.

2460
01:29:21,451 --> 01:29:24,091
I've never seen things like this before.

2461
01:29:25,091 --> 01:29:26,331
(Dabbing)

2462
01:29:27,031 --> 01:29:28,661
Wait, Jong Min.

2463
01:29:28,761 --> 01:29:30,961
(He calls out to Jong Min.)

2464
01:29:31,161 --> 01:29:33,601
I told you to dab it once, but why do you keep... Look.

2465
01:29:34,631 --> 01:29:36,240
You touched this again, right?

2466
01:29:36,241 --> 01:29:37,547
(He is caught touching the blossoms twice.)

2467
01:29:37,571 --> 01:29:39,541
You touched this twice.

2468
01:29:39,641 --> 01:29:41,040
- I saw everything.
- Really?

2469
01:29:41,041 --> 01:29:43,640
- Go with your gut.
- Go with your gut.

2470
01:29:43,641 --> 01:29:45,161
(Let's try it again with gut feeling.)

2471
01:29:45,341 --> 01:29:48,080
All Se Yoon did was eat this week.

2472
01:29:48,081 --> 01:29:50,821
Totally. He just shot eating shows.

2473
01:29:51,221 --> 01:29:53,450
- Hello.
- Hello.

2474
01:29:53,451 --> 01:29:54,590
(That's correct. He's enjoying a food tour now.)

2475
01:29:54,591 --> 01:29:56,991
They have the ttukbaegi dish.

2476
01:29:57,321 --> 01:29:59,731
- Duck soup ttukbaegi.
- Can we have ttukbaegi?

2477
01:29:59,891 --> 01:30:00,961
Yes.

2478
01:30:01,161 --> 01:30:02,561
How much is it?

2479
01:30:02,761 --> 01:30:04,760
- How much is it?
- It's ten dollars.

2480
01:30:04,761 --> 01:30:05,841
- Ten dollars?
- Seriously?

2481
01:30:06,231 --> 01:30:07,431
Only ten dollars?

2482
01:30:07,831 --> 01:30:09,471
Really? Is it?

2483
01:30:09,841 --> 01:30:11,540
We will have two.

2484
01:30:11,541 --> 01:30:12,640
(Let's eat.)

2485
01:30:12,641 --> 01:30:14,041
We're just lucky.

2486
01:30:14,711 --> 01:30:17,210
There are bones. I see the wings.

2487
01:30:17,211 --> 01:30:19,051
(Served in an earthen pot, it is even hotter.)

2488
01:30:19,111 --> 01:30:20,610
(Here comes the nourishing duck soup.)

2489
01:30:20,611 --> 01:30:22,581
It has big pieces of meat.

2490
01:30:22,951 --> 01:30:26,081
Look at the duck meat. Oh, dear.

2491
01:30:27,921 --> 01:30:29,120
With some water parsley.

2492
01:30:29,121 --> 01:30:31,321
(With slightly cooked water parsley)

2493
01:30:32,291 --> 01:30:34,161
(A bit bite)

2494
01:30:35,761 --> 01:30:37,801
(This is it.)

2495
01:30:38,661 --> 01:30:42,031
(Seon Ho tries the soup first.)

2496
01:30:42,901 --> 01:30:45,471
(I love it.)

2497
01:30:45,601 --> 01:30:48,040
I thought it would be spicy, but it's actually mild.

2498
01:30:48,041 --> 01:30:49,941
(The refreshing and light soup is superb.)

2499
01:30:50,441 --> 01:30:52,641
The duck and water parsley go so well together.

2500
01:30:54,511 --> 01:30:58,551
(Duck and water parsley are a perfect match.)

2501
01:30:59,481 --> 01:31:04,121
(They've fallen in love with the duck soup after a bite.)

2502
01:31:07,091 --> 01:31:10,901
(Clapping automatically)

2503
01:31:11,701 --> 01:31:14,570
(How about a bowl of duck soup for dinner tonight?)

2504
01:31:14,571 --> 01:31:16,841
I'm eating a lot today.

2505
01:31:17,741 --> 01:31:19,611
Is the other team having a hard time?

2506
01:31:20,411 --> 01:31:21,651
They will work for a long time.

2507
01:31:21,871 --> 01:31:22,941
- For a long time?
- Yes.

2508
01:31:23,681 --> 01:31:25,081
I'm so happy that DinDin lost.

2509
01:31:25,341 --> 01:31:27,311
It serves him right. It feels so good.

2510
01:31:27,751 --> 01:31:29,820
I'm not sure if he can reach pear trees.

2511
01:31:29,821 --> 01:31:31,750
Gosh, it feels great.

2512
01:31:31,751 --> 01:31:33,721
(While they are enjoying a satisfying breakfast)

2513
01:31:34,221 --> 01:31:36,761
Hey, you didn't do the middle one, right?

2514
01:31:36,991 --> 01:31:38,021
I was doing it.

2515
01:31:39,221 --> 01:31:41,991
(The bees have finished more than half of the work.)

2516
01:31:42,631 --> 01:31:46,161
(They have become noticeably quieter.)

2517
01:31:46,871 --> 01:31:48,301
Gosh, my shoulders hurt.

2518
01:31:48,501 --> 01:31:50,900
This puts a lot more strain on my shoulders than I thought.

2519
01:31:50,901 --> 01:31:53,171
- We should keep our arms raised.
- And my neck hurts.

2520
01:31:53,241 --> 01:31:55,671
Oh, dear. My bees.

2521
01:31:56,141 --> 01:31:57,311
"My bees."

2522
01:31:57,481 --> 01:31:59,080
(Just then, the boss appears holding something in his hands.)

2523
01:31:59,081 --> 01:32:01,450
- We're not even humans.
- Good work, everyone.

2524
01:32:01,451 --> 01:32:03,280
You think of us as bees.

2525
01:32:03,281 --> 01:32:05,780
- I brought some snacks.
- We're bees.

2526
01:32:05,781 --> 01:32:07,250
- Snacks?
- Yes.

2527
01:32:07,251 --> 01:32:08,920
- It's pear juice.
- Pear juice?

2528
01:32:08,921 --> 01:32:11,521
We don't have pears yet.

2529
01:32:12,421 --> 01:32:14,430
It's the best for hangovers.

2530
01:32:14,431 --> 01:32:15,460
That's nice.

2531
01:32:15,461 --> 01:32:18,330
Balloon flower root, loofah,

2532
01:32:18,331 --> 01:32:20,231
- and ginger juice is added.
- Loofah?

2533
01:32:20,571 --> 01:32:22,830
- Just try it.
- It sounds very healthy.

2534
01:32:22,831 --> 01:32:24,641
It's really healthy.

2535
01:32:24,801 --> 01:32:26,910
- It's usually...
- It's nice.

2536
01:32:26,911 --> 01:32:28,241
It's sweet.

2537
01:32:28,341 --> 01:32:30,080
This must be good for hangovers.

2538
01:32:30,081 --> 01:32:31,580
- It is.
- It's sweet.

2539
01:32:31,581 --> 01:32:32,911
And it has a lot of moisture.

2540
01:32:33,811 --> 01:32:35,650
Hurry and bear fruit soon.

2541
01:32:35,651 --> 01:32:36,897
(After recharging with pear juice)

2542
01:32:36,921 --> 01:32:39,020
Jong Min should bear fruit, too.

2543
01:32:39,021 --> 01:32:40,021
I know.

2544
01:32:40,022 --> 01:32:41,727
(The members are giving it their all until the very end.)

2545
01:32:41,751 --> 01:32:43,490
Doesn't this feel like something a fairy would do?

2546
01:32:43,491 --> 01:32:46,061
Right. We touch it gently.

2547
01:32:46,121 --> 01:32:47,831
We're fairies, indeed.

2548
01:32:48,491 --> 01:32:50,231
Let's keep going.

2549
01:32:51,431 --> 01:32:52,431
(Today's quota)

2550
01:32:52,432 --> 01:32:54,330
- Good work.
- Good work.

2551
01:32:54,331 --> 01:32:55,500
I'll try Naju pears later.

2552
01:32:55,501 --> 01:32:57,540
You should come and pick the pears later.

2553
01:32:57,541 --> 01:32:58,870
We will.

2554
01:32:58,871 --> 01:32:59,970
- Thank you for today.
- Thank you.

2555
01:32:59,971 --> 01:33:01,170
Thank you.

2556
01:33:01,171 --> 01:33:02,331
(The rewarding work is over.)

2557
01:33:02,671 --> 01:33:04,141
Guess which one is the flower.

2558
01:33:04,481 --> 01:33:07,951
Double the happiness, double the joy in the fragrant spring breeze.

2559
01:33:08,581 --> 01:33:10,851
This sweet place enjoyed twice as much with pears.

2560
01:33:11,551 --> 01:33:13,791
Come visit Naju, South Jeolla Province!

2561
01:33:13,951 --> 01:33:15,391
Korea's best...

2562
01:33:15,851 --> 01:33:18,460
Real wild road variety show!

2563
01:33:18,461 --> 01:33:19,561
Who are we?

2564
01:33:19,761 --> 01:33:23,200
- 2 Days 1 Night!
- 2 Days 1 Night!

2565
01:33:23,201 --> 01:33:26,731
(2 Days 1 Night)

2566
01:33:26,901 --> 01:33:28,771
(Next episode)

2567
01:33:29,201 --> 01:33:31,441
(When a genius joins a group where everyone is a fool, )

2568
01:33:31,571 --> 01:33:33,811
(he becomes the odd one out?)

2569
01:33:34,141 --> 01:33:35,510
(He's been annoying in this group of fools.)

2570
01:33:35,511 --> 01:33:36,581
(Condescending DinDin)

2571
01:33:36,641 --> 01:33:37,741
I'm so furious.

2572
01:33:38,341 --> 01:33:40,481
(The Rat-catching Alliance is formed.)

2573
01:33:41,081 --> 01:33:43,151
(And so begins the war of fools.)

2574
01:33:43,621 --> 01:33:45,351
(The rat-catching begins in earnest.)

2575
01:33:46,451 --> 01:33:47,851
(We will catch him no matter what!)

2576
01:33:48,121 --> 01:33:49,450
(They are no match for me.)

2577
01:33:49,451 --> 01:33:50,490
(Condescending)

2578
01:33:50,491 --> 01:33:51,790
We must catch DinDin.

2579
01:33:51,791 --> 01:33:53,990
(To catch Condescending Rat DinDin)

2580
01:33:53,991 --> 01:33:56,031
- Don't show it to DinDin.
- Let me see.

2581
01:33:56,061 --> 01:33:59,201
(Their desperate struggle)

2582
01:33:59,401 --> 01:34:01,101
(You can't catch me, can you?)

2583
01:34:01,771 --> 01:34:03,200
- You think you're the best, right?
- Attack him!

2584
01:34:03,201 --> 01:34:05,401
(Will they be able to catch Rat DinDin?)

2585
01:34:05,541 --> 01:34:07,640
- Catch the rat, squeak, squeak.
- Catch the rat, squeak, squeak.

2586
01:34:07,641 --> 01:34:08,917
- Catch the rat.
- Catch the rat, squeak, squeak.

2587
01:34:08,941 --> 01:34:11,411
(See you next week.)
